<p>Ancible Play Book Instructions</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"><span class="no">Docker</span> <span class="n">installations</span>
<span class="no">Docker</span> <span class="no">File</span> <span class="no">Explained</span>
<span class="no">Docker</span> <span class="no">File</span> <span class="no">Testing</span></code></pre></figure>

<p>Play book will consist of tasks that are executed by ansible. Playbook can be viewed as an instruction manual for ansible. It is readable as a text and also executable as a programing language.</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">print_hi</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">name</span><span class="p">)</span>
  <span class="nb">puts</span> <span class="s2">"Hi, </span><span class="si">#{</span><span class="nb">name</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s2">"</span>
<span class="k">end</span>
<span class="n">print_hi</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'Tom'</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="c1">#=&gt; prints 'Hi, Tom' to STDOUT.</span></code></pre></figure>

